ZCZC GE85
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 252300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE CENTRED IN THE NORWEGIAN BASIN
1029. THIS ANTICYCLONE WILL REMAIN SLOW MOV THROUGH THE PERIOD. FURTHER HIGH
PRESSURE CENTRED OVER THE CONTINENT WILL EXTEND NWARDS INTO THE N SEA. HIGH
PRESSURE WILL SLWY DECLINE THROUGH THE PERIOD BUT STILL MAINTAIN INFLUENCE
OVER MOST OF THE N SEA.
MEANWHILE A LARGE COMPLEX DEEP LOW 973 CENTRED AROUND
47 N 33 W WILL VERY SLWY MOV N-EWARDS AND WILL PUSH FRONTAL TROUGHS INTO
THE NW OF THE UK DURING WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE FCST
TO AFFECT CULLERCOATS AT FIRST HOWEVER OVERNIGHT TUESDAY INTO WEDNESDAY
STRG EERLIES WILL DEVELOP IN SEA AREA FAIR ISLE. THESE WILL STRENGTHEN TO
GALE FORCE LATER ON WEDNESDAY. DURING THURSDAY THESE STRG WINDS AND GALES
WILL SLWY DECLINE NWARDS
